    "body": "### Problem\n\nfirstly i'm sorry, it's just my imagination. language servers could be malicious, applying [change.kind={create,delete}](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/release-0.10/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua#L820) without any checking could cause security issues, for instance, `rm -rf $HOME`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n[the implementation of lsp.util.apply_workspace_edit](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/release-0.10/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua#L819)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIMHO, any changes in a workspace_edit response should only happen under the client.workspace_folders, maybe it's worth to ask user's confirmation or log or idk (sometime client.workspace_folders could be nil).\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nnvim 0.10\n\n### Language server name/version\n\npyright\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
